01:06:55.119 --> 01:07:30.480
And I'm not knocking network marketing, but it was always pushed around people: 'Sell this, sell this.

01:07:30.480 --> 01:08:01.188
' Amway and Young Living and this and that, and everybody's selling everything.

01:08:01.188 --> 01:08:22.950
In the body of Christ, network marketing is everything.

01:09:11.020 --> 01:09:11.440
We had this group over there...

01:09:11.440 --> 01:09:14.940
I remember it.

01:09:16.660 --> 01:09:36.795
You go into a mega-church like I was at; you had every hall down there.

01:10:01.452 --> 01:10:02.697
We had rooms full of people always talking about network marketing.

01:10:02.697 --> 01:10:08.140
'Don't you want to sell this?

01:10:08.140 --> 01:10:10.539
Well, we got this MaxGXL...

01:10:10.539 --> 01:10:21.902
' I mean, there are so many things people are trying to push.

01:10:21.902 --> 01:11:07.936
'We'll put the man of God at the head of the pyramid so this whole thing will be blessed, and we'll all sow into this and it'll bless the church.

01:11:07.936 --> 01:11:14.440
' And then, boom!

01:11:26.298 --> 01:11:51.660
And then one thing happened—it was a gas card thing—and everybody was busted by the FBI and they went to prison.

01:11:51.660 --> 01:12:30.880
I believe that was a hoax or something; there are all kinds of things that people had going on over the years.

01:12:30.880 --> 01:12:39.586
And you look at it and go, 'I don't know.

01:12:39.586 --> 01:12:42.217
' Just my thinking.

01:12:42.217 --> 01:12:45.560
God help us all get wisdom.

01:12:45.560 --> 01:13:03.369
In all that you do, get wisdom and get some common sense and meditate on His word, and it will change you from the inside out.

01:13:03.369 --> 01:13:10.107
He's never failed you.

01:13:10.107 --> 01:13:17.302
He will always take care of you.

01:13:17.302 --> 01:13:31.680
But you have to be listening to that still, small voice inside of you and not listen to all the prophetic nonsense on the internet.

01:13:31.680 --> 01:13:40.040
Listen to the still, small voice on the inside of you.

01:13:40.040 --> 01:13:47.634
Get in this word, and it will change you from the inside out.

01:13:47.634 --> 01:13:55.046
There's no microwave to it.

01:13:55.056 --> 01:14:02.500
Quit trying to be lazy.

01:14:13.759 --> 01:14:14.719
You either do it or you don't.

01:14:14.719 --> 01:14:22.626
But there are no spiritual shortcuts.

01:14:22.626 --> 01:14:24.560
Do you understand?

01:14:24.560 --> 01:14:36.089
There are no spiritual shortcuts, ladies and gentlemen.

01:15:18.880 --> 01:15:19.170
It's called a slow cooker.

01:15:19.170 --> 01:15:28.310
'Seek Me daily and you will find Me.

01:15:28.320 --> 01:15:32.651
Knock and the door will be opened unto you.

01:15:32.651 --> 01:15:35.240
' Do you understand?

01:15:35.240 --> 01:15:40.148
It's not a 777 lottery number and a microwave.

01:15:40.148 --> 01:15:43.619
It doesn't come that way.

01:15:43.619 --> 01:15:46.320
It comes by refining.

01:16:10.560 --> 01:16:15.838
And refining fire is what changes you.

01:16:15.838 --> 01:16:29.117
That is the sufferings for the greater glory.

01:16:29.117 --> 01:16:35.679
But people don't want that.

01:16:35.679 --> 01:16:43.440
They say, 'Well, I want a double portion of your anointing.

01:16:43.440 --> 01:16:53.510
' You know how many people have asked me for that?

01:16:53.520 --> 01:17:14.000
'Now, Brandon, lay hands on me so I can have a double portion.

01:17:14.000 --> 01:17:15.886
I need impartation.

01:17:15.886 --> 01:17:18.880
' You know what it's called?

01:17:18.880 --> 01:17:22.239
Knee time.

01:17:22.239 --> 01:17:24.532
That's impartation: knee time.

01:17:24.532 --> 01:17:29.440
Spend time with Him.

01:17:29.440 --> 01:17:35.600
There are no shortcuts.

01:17:35.600 --> 01:17:48.192
'I want to go to the front of the line.

01:17:48.192 --> 01:17:58.427
' Well, so did I twenty-five years ago.

01:17:58.427 --> 01:18:03.759
But when you go through the valley, you learn to thirst.

01:18:06.480 --> 01:18:07.806
All right, let's go.

01:18:07.806 --> 01:18:09.794
That's enough.

01:18:54.560 --> 01:18:57.155
Oh, Lord, help me.

01:18:57.155 --> 01:19:09.155
Father, I thank You for the body.

01:19:09.155 --> 01:19:32.118
Who wants to take communion and pray now?

01:19:32.118 --> 01:19:59.110
But I felt it in my heart to say it.

01:19:59.120 --> 01:20:09.235
You must know the truth.

01:20:09.235 --> 01:21:37.676
And Jesus wants you to be successful in every area of your life.

01:21:37.676 --> 01:22:41.510
He loves you from Scripture.

01:22:41.520 --> 01:22:43.520
Look.

01:22:43.520 --> 01:23:20.000
Here you go.

01:24:22.960 --> 01:24:23.160
You can just read it.

01:24:23.160 --> 01:24:27.599
And if you want to show it, you can.

01:24:27.599 --> 01:24:31.680
Now, I want you to see the Sooner.

01:24:31.680 --> 01:24:34.639
We had Japan sign the deal.

01:24:34.639 --> 01:24:43.635
And now look who's here: South Korea.

01:24:43.635 --> 01:24:49.680
Japan, South Korea.

01:24:49.680 --> 01:24:54.736
Remember I told you?

01:24:54.736 --> 01:24:55.760
Sooners.

01:25:06.289 --> 01:25:06.719
The Sooners.

01:25:06.719 --> 01:25:13.080
Now look what they say right here.

01:25:13.080 --> 01:25:18.000
Now look at their flag.

01:25:18.240 --> 01:25:19.199
You see it?

01:25:34.629 --> 01:25:34.937
The Sooners.

01:25:34.937 --> 01:25:36.480
Boomer Schooner wagon.

01:25:36.480 --> 01:25:42.178
Remember the Lord said, 'Watch South Korea.

01:25:42.178 --> 01:25:43.376
Watch Japan.

01:25:43.376 --> 01:25:47.713
' It's happening just like He said.

01:25:47.713 --> 01:25:55.194
That's neat, Braden.

01:26:05.394 --> 01:26:05.657
You should have told me that earlier.

01:26:05.657 --> 01:26:09.977
We could have done a dance together.

01:26:09.977 --> 01:26:10.549
Wow.

01:26:22.880 --> 01:26:23.314
I didn't know until now—until you were doing that—and I started looking.

01:26:38.663 --> 01:26:38.925
I started waking up.

01:26:52.000 --> 01:26:52.360
I started getting all the stuff from Braden.

01:26:52.360 --> 01:26:54.746
Oh, Jesus, He's so wonderful.

01:26:55.333 --> 01:26:57.383
The Sooners, huh?

01:26:57.383 --> 01:27:00.310
Yeah.

01:27:00.320 --> 01:27:04.560
Isn't Jesus wonderful?

01:27:04.560 --> 01:27:13.493
Accuracy is important, and I don't want to be flaky spiritually.

01:27:13.493 --> 01:27:30.550
Leading all these people like the Lord let us do, we don't want to be flaky.

01:27:35.840 --> 01:27:38.079
And we can miss it.

01:27:38.079 --> 01:27:44.360
But isn't it nice to see it happening?

01:27:44.360 --> 01:27:47.466
Oh, what a plan.

01:27:47.466 --> 01:27:58.658
Like Sister Billye always says, 'Oh, what a plan!

01:27:58.658 --> 01:28:02.089
Oh, what a plan!

01:28:02.089 --> 01:28:04.133
Oh, what a plan!

01:28:04.133 --> 01:28:06.420
Oh, what a planner, Brandon!

01:28:06.420 --> 01:28:08.940
Oh, what a plan!

01:28:08.940 --> 01:28:11.049
Oh, what a planner!

01:28:11.049 --> 01:28:15.102
' Father, we just thank You for it.

01:28:15.102 --> 01:28:19.160
It is all over Las Vegas.

01:28:19.160 --> 01:28:19.820
What?

01:28:19.820 --> 01:28:23.420
Yeah, and it's right.

01:28:23.420 --> 01:28:25.220
Probably nothing though, right?

01:28:25.220 --> 01:28:35.988
Not financial advice here.

01:28:35.988 --> 01:28:41.679
Just showing you the news.

01:28:41.679 --> 01:29:03.084
When you pray for something as much as I pray for some things, when you see it in the news, it blesses me.

01:29:42.853 --> 01:29:43.138
I spend hours praying over things the Lord gives me, and you see fruit of your prayers.

01:29:56.480 --> 01:29:56.773
You see it all over the buildings.

01:29:56.773 --> 01:29:58.240
What's that at?

01:29:58.240 --> 01:29:58.827
$140.

01:29:58.827 --> 01:30:00.133
That's interesting.

01:30:16.089 --> 01:30:16.619
It doesn't matter.

01:30:16.619 --> 01:30:18.119
All right.

01:30:18.119 --> 01:30:20.319
Let's take communion.

01:30:20.319 --> 01:30:22.800
Do you have anything else?

01:30:22.800 --> 01:30:24.380
No, go ahead.

01:30:24.380 --> 01:30:27.479
Oh, you need to see this now.

01:30:27.479 --> 01:30:29.039
This is important.

01:30:29.039 --> 01:30:33.165
Okay, and then we'll go to pray.

01:30:33.165 --> 01:30:39.799
This is about the drought the Lord warned us about.

01:30:41.600 --> 01:30:52.140
The worst snowpack in how many years in Colorado?

01:30:52.140 --> 01:30:59.839
Now listen to this man talk about the snowpack in Denver.

01:31:27.973 --> 01:31:28.426
This is the Antero Reservoir in Colorado.

01:31:28.426 --> 01:31:33.147
In a few weeks, all of this will be empty.

01:31:33.147 --> 01:31:44.439
Denver Water is draining it, not because something's wrong with the reservoir, but because of the drought, and that means millions of fish could die as well.

01:31:44.439 --> 01:31:49.280
Antero has the highest evaporation rate of any reservoir for Denver Water.

01:31:49.280 --> 01:31:53.1000
Part of that is because it's so shallow.

01:31:53.1000 --> 01:32:04.859
But this year's Colorado snowpack was one of the worst in recorded history, and Denver Water needs more water.

01:32:04.859 --> 01:32:09.440
They need to conserve everything that they can.

01:32:09.440 --> 01:32:20.704
So they're moving the water from here to Cheesman Reservoir where water evaporates slower.

01:32:20.704 --> 01:32:45.490
It'll save enough water for about 15,000 households to have enough water for a year.

01:32:45.490 --> 01:32:59.590
But before that can happen, Colorado Parks and Wildlife is asking as many people as possible to come fish here before the water is gone.

01:33:07.510 --> 01:33:08.040
No bag limits on any species through May 13th.

01:33:08.040 --> 01:33:13.288
All of these fish are going to die.

01:33:13.288 --> 01:33:21.340
Everything—I mean, even the fish that everybody keeps, they're going to die.

01:33:21.340 --> 01:33:29.467
Whatever people don't come and take, the fish are going to be in the bottom of the lake.

01:33:29.467 --> 01:33:37.459
They're going to be bone-dry skeletons by next year.

01:33:37.459 --> 01:33:45.413
Travis Sawyer is a fishing guide here.

01:33:50.791 --> 01:33:55.680
He says he's running free trips for people so that they can enjoy the water while it's still here.

01:33:55.680 --> 01:34:05.760
This is one of his favorite places to fish, and he says that people from all over the world fly here for the fish.

01:34:05.760 --> 01:34:09.440
He said, 'We're draining this lake bone dry.

01:34:09.440 --> 01:34:23.640
' So anything that people don't take is going to be killed.

01:34:30.113 --> 01:34:43.616
The last time that Antero was drained was 2015 for a dam rehabilitation project.

01:34:43.616 --> 01:34:46.789
Before that, it was 2002, also a drought year.

01:34:46.789 --> 01:34:52.731
It took several years for the fish to become healthy again here after that.

01:34:52.731 --> 01:34:56.720
We've had bad droughts before, but nothing like this one.

01:34:56.720 --> 01:35:00.740
I'm Mark.

01:35:15.480 --> 01:35:15.700
I cover Colorado.

01:35:15.700 --> 01:35:36.111
Follow for more stories like this one.

01:35:36.111 --> 01:35:44.069
So, all those fish—if you like fish and you live in Colorado, that might be a fun day.

01:36:18.738 --> 01:36:19.156
I love fishing.

01:36:19.991 --> 01:36:24.960
And I tell you what, that would be a fun day for me.

01:36:24.960 --> 01:36:30.231
I'd put all those things in an ice chest and freeze them.

01:36:30.231 --> 01:36:37.044
There's nothing better than trout to me.

01:36:37.044 --> 01:36:43.573
In fact, my slobber comes just thinking about it.

01:36:43.573 --> 01:36:48.624
I've been eating protein shakes and little bits of chicken.

01:36:48.624 --> 01:36:55.085
Oh, good Lord, I'm trying to get this weight down as fast as I can.

01:36:55.085 --> 01:36:57.875
But I walked five miles yesterday.

01:37:10.320 --> 01:37:10.606
I was really excited about it.

01:37:26.319 --> 01:37:26.613
I told Diana my face felt like charcoal.

01:37:26.613 --> 01:37:39.970
But five miles in a day is pretty good for Brandon Biggs.

01:37:39.970 --> 01:37:41.080
All right.

01:37:41.080 --> 01:37:43.546
Look what Jesus is doing.

01:37:43.546 --> 01:37:46.266
In Russia, Putin is scheming.

01:37:46.266 --> 01:37:58.311
Father, we just thank you for the body as we come before you boldly into your throne.

01:37:58.311 --> 01:38:10.760
Father, if you want to show us things about that which is to come, we're here.

01:38:10.760 --> 01:38:17.748
We're always here just to stay by your feet and say, 'God, we love you.

01:38:17.748 --> 01:38:20.520
' We want to hear everything.

01:38:20.520 --> 01:38:28.533
I'll sit in your lap and just listen to your heartbeat and your breath.

01:38:28.533 --> 01:38:41.463
Every breath that proceeds out of you, Father, I want to be close to you.

01:38:41.463 --> 01:38:57.051
Father, I thank you that we hear you and a stranger's voice we will not follow.

01:38:57.051 --> 01:39:07.960
We lift up this body, God, and we're so thankful for your son, Jesus.

01:39:07.960 --> 01:39:33.040
Thank you, Father, that he suffered and died for every single one of us, that we walk in victory.

01:39:33.040 --> 01:39:41.760
Thank you, Lord, that we go from glory to glory.

01:40:03.880 --> 01:40:04.140
I thank you, Lord, that we are healed and whole and well.

01:40:04.140 --> 01:40:41.100
We don't have to have sickness and disease in our bodies anymore because by your stripes, we're healed.

01:40:41.100 --> 01:40:56.749
We take this body in the name of Jesus and we give you all the glory, honor, and praise for what you did for us.

01:40:56.749 --> 01:40:57.369
Amen.

01:40:57.369 --> 01:41:08.560
We apply the blood of Jesus over us and we thank you, Father, that it never loses its power.

01:41:14.263 --> 01:41:25.840
It covers us from the top of our head to the soles of our feet, uninterrupted and unhindered by any satanic or demonic force.

01:41:25.840 --> 01:41:29.760
We rebuke the devil in the name of Jesus.

01:41:29.760 --> 01:41:30.560
Amen.

01:41:30.560 --> 01:41:34.133
Over our children, our wives, and our finances.

01:41:34.133 --> 01:41:37.340
Father, open the eyes of our heart.

01:41:37.340 --> 01:42:14.380
I want to see you high and lifted up, shining in the light of your glory.

01:42:14.380 --> 01:42:24.000
Pour out your power and love as we sing holy, holy, holy.

01:42:24.000 --> 01:42:26.811
I want to see you.

01:42:26.811 --> 01:42:37.540
Lord, there are so many people here tonight that are thirsty.

01:42:37.540 --> 01:42:49.973
We lift up our cup before you and say, 'Fill it.

01:42:49.973 --> 01:42:56.829
' Come and quench this thirsting of our soul.

01:42:56.829 --> 01:43:02.446
Bread of heaven, feed us till we want no more.

01:43:25.360 --> 01:43:27.920
Fill our cup, fill it up, and make us whole.

01:43:27.920 --> 01:43:34.159
If I could just sit with you a while.

01:43:34.159 --> 01:43:49.600
I need you to hold me moment by moment till forever passes by.

01:43:49.600 --> 01:43:52.343
Fill the cups of those here tonight.

01:43:52.343 --> 01:43:54.200
They're so thirsty, Holy Spirit.

01:43:54.200 --> 01:43:56.600
Do what you do best.

01:43:56.600 --> 01:44:04.192
We're wall-to-wall, Holy Ghost, and we yield to that tonight.

01:44:04.192 --> 01:44:06.760
We yield to you.

01:44:06.760 --> 01:44:14.310
Become so real.

01:44:14.320 --> 01:44:23.840
The tangible, weighty presence of the Lord that changes you from the inside out.

01:44:23.840 --> 01:44:27.359
Do what you do best, oh God.

01:44:27.359 --> 01:44:33.131
Fill the cup.

01:44:33.131 --> 01:44:37.898
Life pulls it, making us dry.

01:44:37.898 --> 01:44:46.080
Life's hardships and circumstances make us dry.

01:44:46.080 --> 01:44:48.064
We leak out.

01:44:48.064 --> 01:45:02.719
But don't just fill it; make it overflow so everybody else can taste and see that the Lord is so good.

01:45:02.719 --> 01:45:07.520
It's the goodness of God that brings men to repentance.

01:45:15.479 --> 01:45:15.859
When they see us, they see Jesus in us.

01:45:15.859 --> 01:45:21.725
Christ in me, the hope of glory.

01:45:21.725 --> 01:45:24.319
We love you.

01:45:24.319 --> 01:45:31.758
Oh, how we love you.

01:45:31.758 --> 01:45:39.947
I'll have no other, for I love you only.

01:45:39.947 --> 01:45:43.500
I'll never forsake you or leave you alone.

01:45:43.500 --> 01:45:46.063
I love you.

01:46:07.440 --> 01:46:07.813
Oh, how I love you.

01:46:07.813 --> 01:46:18.480
Here in your arms, I'll always be at rest in your precious love you have for me.

01:46:18.480 --> 01:46:22.080
We worship you.

01:46:22.080 --> 01:46:24.080
We're so grateful.

01:46:24.080 --> 01:46:32.639
We take the care out of our prayers.

01:46:40.960 --> 01:47:44.867
The cares of this life try to choke out everything: cares for finances, health, marriages, our kids, work, where we live, and where we go to church.

01:47:44.867 --> 01:47:51.679
There are so many cares.

01:48:34.110 --> 01:48:37.560
The cares try to choke out everything, but we cast our cares upon you tonight.

01:48:37.560 --> 01:48:38.599
We give it to you.

01:48:38.599 --> 01:48:42.409
We don't need to carry it anyway.

01:48:42.409 --> 01:48:46.960
We cast our cares on you, for you care for us.

01:48:46.960 --> 01:48:59.120
We're so grateful for all that you've done, all you've provided, all you've done for our health, for our bodies, for everything.

01:48:59.120 --> 01:50:33.040
Even when we don't see the full manifestation of what we've been believing for yet, God, you are still so faithful to us.

01:50:33.040 --> 01:51:12.080
We're not moved by what we see.

01:51:12.080 --> 01:52:01.109
We're not moved by what we feel.

01:52:01.119 --> 01:52:16.880
We're moved by what the word of God says.

01:52:16.880 --> 01:52:32.799
And we're fully persuaded that what God, you have promised, you are able also to perform.

01:52:32.799 --> 01:52:51.360
And we take the care out of our prayer.

01:52:51.360 --> 01:53:18.239
But with thanksgiving, we let our requests be made known unto you.

01:53:18.239 --> 01:53:24.550
Thank you, Father.

01:53:24.550 --> 01:53:32.673
There were stipulations before it: with thanksgiving.

01:53:32.673 --> 01:53:41.248
We thank him first.

01:53:41.248 --> 01:54:41.520
We praise him first, for he knows what we have need of before we even ask.

01:55:08.971 --> 01:55:09.257
We thank him first with thanksgiving.

01:55:10.800 --> 01:55:14.600
We take the care out of our prayer, but with thanksgiving.

01:55:16.550 --> 01:55:17.660
Thank you, Lord.

01:55:21.760 --> 01:55:23.850
A thankful heart moves the Father.

01:55:23.850 --> 01:55:26.719
It is giving a grateful attitude.

01:55:31.800 --> 01:55:33.173
Thank you for even the things we don't see manifested yet in our lives.

01:55:33.173 --> 01:55:36.133
We're so grateful for what we do have.

01:55:36.133 --> 01:55:40.760
We're so thankful for where we are.

01:55:46.040 --> 01:55:46.320
And we're so grateful that we're not where we were.

01:55:46.320 --> 01:55:49.154
For we're going from glory to glory.

01:56:01.806 --> 01:56:02.137
Lord, we're so grateful, Father, that you would visit us, that you call us your own.

01:56:03.520 --> 01:56:06.480
You adopted us and you accepted us into your house.

01:56:13.493 --> 01:56:21.805
And you said, "I make you my own joint heirs with Jesus Christ.

01:56:21.805 --> 01:56:23.479
" Thank you, Father.

01:56:23.479 --> 01:56:27.359
As he is, so are we in this world.

01:56:27.359 --> 01:56:31.474
Greater works will we do because he goes unto the Father.

01:56:31.474 --> 01:56:36.239
He sent us a Comforter, the Holy Spirit.

01:56:36.239 --> 01:56:39.419
He dwells on the inside of us.

01:56:39.419 --> 01:56:42.779
When Christ sat down, we sat down with him.

01:56:44.400 --> 01:56:44.600
Thank you, Father.

01:56:48.853 --> 01:56:52.610
The same Holy Spirit that raised Jesus Christ from the dead dwells on the inside of me.

01:56:52.610 --> 01:56:57.119
He dwells on the inside of me richly by faith.

01:56:57.119 --> 01:56:58.240
I'm wall-to-wall Holy Ghost.

01:56:58.240 --> 01:57:01.783
Can these bones live—the dry bones upon this earth?

01:57:16.509 --> 01:57:16.719
Can these bones live?

01:57:16.719 --> 01:57:20.434
They can, and they will, and they do.

01:57:32.213 --> 01:57:32.600
We speak to the dry bones in the church.

